MALE (
Fig. 21–25
). Similar to adult female except: genital opening situated between coxae IV; aedeagus present; with a pair of anal suckers; without adanal setae; tarsus IV having 2 suckers. Complement of setae on legs as in adult female except tarsi IV with 3 + 1 dorsoapical spine + 3–5 ventroapical spines.
